# <%= current_page.data.title %>

Any developer added to [hmcts org](https://github.com/hmcts) would be able to create a new Github repo.


1. Naming convention for repository name is `{product}-{component}`.
2. Choose from a template in the drop down depending on whether it's a front end or backend component. These templates provide all the boiler plate code needed for a new app. 
    - [spring-boot-template](https://github.com/hmcts/spring-boot-template)
    - [expressjs-template](https://github.com/hmcts/expressjs-template)
3. Repository should be public.
4. Give permissions to GitHub teams created in [Team Onboarding](/onboarding/team/#github-config)
    <table>
     <tr>
